def: To cover with a thin layer, as objects of glass with glass of adifferent color. See Flashing, n., 3 (b).
Not wearing a coat; also, not possessing a coat.
That excerpts, selects, or chooses. D. L. Mackenzie.
Productive of fruit, or causing fruit to be developed.
The decimal part of a logarithm, as distinguished from theintegral part, or characteristic.
To inclose, or nearly inclose, as a harbor or a vessel, withland.
Sizelike; viscous; glutinous; as, sizy blood. Arbuthnot.
Serving to coagulate; produced by coagulation; as, coagulatoryeffects. Boyle.
A kind of tobacco for smoking, made of the dried leaves,coarsely broken; -- so called from the rush baskets in which it ispacked in South America. McElrath.
